simulator.checkout

Class AbstractRegister

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulator.checkout.AbstractRegister

  • public abstract class AbstractRegister
extends java.lang.Object

    A AbstractRegister is used to process Shoppers. A AbstractRegister has a running cost associated with it. Each time a Shopper is processed, a AbstractRegister will produce a Transaction. The running cost of a register is associated with the skill level of the employee working at the register. That means, the faster the employee is able to process a transaction, the higher the running cost will be.

    To implement a AbstractRegister one must implement the createTransaction(Shopper) method.

    Author:
    jcollard, jddevaug
